2/11/19, 11:49 PM - Juan Barbosa: The extraction and quantification of food components, such as proteins, is of vital importance for the nutritional aspects of medicine and, in general, for biochemistry itself. In the present document two samples of common foods, wheat and egg, which have been in the diet of humans for a long time, were studied by means of UV-VIS spectroscopy. Wheat flour was one of the first foods discovered by human civilization and has been one of the main sources of polysaccharides, lipids and proteins since then. Furthermore, eggs have been, since ancient times, a very important food for man and its consumption is widespread worldwide currently. Depending on their function, proteins can be classified as structural, metabolic and storage proteins, like gluten, which is found commonly in wheat flour. Although the results show significant variance, protein content was quantified between 0.706 g and 0.284 g per 100 g of wheat, and 10 mg/mL and 110 mg/mL for egg.
2/11/19, 11:49 PM - Juan Barbosa: con tu nuevo parrafo,
2/11/19, 11:49 PM - Juan Barbosa: The extraction and quantification of food components, such as proteins, is of vital importance for the nutritional aspects of medicine and, in general, for biochemistry itself. In the present document two samples of common foods, wheat and egg, which have been in the diet of humans for a long time, were studied by means of UV-VIS spectroscopy. For this purpose, we carried out the corresponding sample preparation, solution and dilutions to make to make a calibration curve later. Wheat flour was one of the first foods discovered by human civilization and has been one of the main sources of polysaccharides, lipids and proteins since then. Furthermore, eggs have been, since ancient times, a very important food for man and its consumption is widespread worldwide currently. Depending on their function, proteins can be classified as structural, metabolic and storage proteins, like gluten, which is found commonly in wheat flour. Although the results show significant variance, protein content was quantified between 0.706 g and 0.284 g per 100 g of wheat, and 10 mg/mL and 110 mg/mL for egg.

3/25/19, 7:48 PM - Meñeñotes 😽: Gram staining is a method used to differentiates bacteria by the chemical and physical properties of their cell walls by detecting peptidoglycan. Peptidoglycan is a polysaccharide present in the wall of gram-positive bacteria, while gram-negative bacteria do not have cellular wall. However, they have two membranes between which is found a small layer of peptidoglycan in small quantities. The process of staining consists of adding crystal violet to the sample which is retained by gram-positive bacteria, while gram-negative are not capable of retaining the dye because of the addition of ethanol which dehydrates the peptidoglycan layer, shrinking and tightening it, which in turn results in the discoloration of the staining. Gram-positive are not decolorized at all because of the natural thickness of its morphology. Additionally, the external membrane of gram-negative bacteria is composed primarily by lipopolysaccharides, which are directly affected by the addition of ethanol to the sample, leaving the peptidoglycan layer exposed to the external environment and making it easy to manipulate. Moreover, lugol  is an iodine solution that, in aqueous solution, dissociates and releases the iodine ion, which in turn forms a complex with the crystal violet dye added at the beginning and makes it possible to wash it out along with the outer membrane of the gram-negative cells. Finally, the latest addition of safranin is made up to dye the gram-negative bacteria that are, by this moment, translucent.

4/1/19, 6:52 PM - Juan Barbosa: Ya bajo
4/1/19, 11:06 PM - Meñeñotes 😽: Por otro lado, es importante resaltar que el diseño de primers supone un punto crítico en la realización de la PCR, puesto que de estos dependerá la amplificación del fragmento de ADN de interés. Para esto es importante tener en cuenta que estas secuencias deben ser únicas, es decir, no deben ser complementarias a otras secuencias del fragmento de interés o permitir la unión de las mismas a posibles contaminantes, puesto que esto asegura una alta especificidad y reproductibilidad de la amplificación. Además, estos deben tener una longitud de entre 15-25 pares de bases, de manera que se pueda asegurar que la secuencia sea única, pero no demasiado como para afectar la temperatura melting (Tm), es decir, la temperatura a la cual el 50% de los primers se encuentran anillados; y la cual a su vez depende de la fuerza iónica de la solución y del tamaño y composición del primer. Adicionalmente, esta secuencia no debe tener fragmentos complementarios entre si, puesto que esto favorece la formación de estructuras secundarias como hairpin Loops y dímeros de primers.

Por otro lado, la proporción Guanina-Citocina (G-C) de la secuencia tambien juega un papel fundamental en el diseño de primers, puesto que es importante que esta tenga una relación alta en comparación con la proporción de Adenina-Timina. Lo anterior debido a que una proporción de entre 45-50% de G-C asegura una buena temperatura de anillaje y estabilidad de hibridación , puesto que estas son pirimidinas que cuentan con un enlace triple. Además, el porcentaje GC debe ser similar entre primers puesto que este afecta la especificidad de hibridación, la Tm y la temperatura de anillaje, de manera que si los primers difieren de Tm, en un rango mayor de 2-3ºC, no anillarán a la misma temperatura, por lo que el proceso de amplificación se verá aectado en mayor medida. Adicionalmente, es importante resaltar que la secuencia 3’ es crítica para el anillaje y amplificación de la secuencia, puesto que esta es la que cuenta con el extremo OH que hace posible el anclaje de la Polimerasa a la secuencia para la posterior amplificación, de forma que este extremo debe tener una alta proporción G-C con el fin de garantizar el correcto anillaje en el sitio de amplificación.

5/30/19, 9:58 PM - Juan Barbosa: Con el piruvato formado, las últimas dos etapas de la fermentación consisten en la formación de acetaldehído y su posterior transformación en etanol. Para pasar de piruvato a acetaldehido, es necesaria la presencia de la piruvato deshidrogenasa (PDC), la cual en presencia de TPP (tiamina pirofosfato) y Mg2+, induce la pérdida del carboxilo en el piruvato. Esto se debe a la formación de puentes de hidrógeno entre el piruvato, y los residuos Asp27, His114, y Thr72 de la PDC. Posteriormente, la carga negativa del residuo Glu473 desestabiliza el grupo carbonilo del piruvato. Con la salida del grupo carbonilo,  un protón es transferido al residuo de ácido glutámico desde el TPP, posteriormente el agua dona un proton al sustrato. Finalmente, los electrones dentro del sustrato se mueven formando un enlace carbonilo con la subsecuente liberación del acetaldehído.

https://doi.org/10.1021/bi901864j

Una vez formado el acetaldehído, la alcohol deshidrogenasa ADH1 reduce el acetaldehído a etanol. Para esto,

5/30/19, 10:51 PM - Meñeñotes 😽: Fermentation is a metabolic process of incomplete oxidation that takes place in the absence of oxygen. This is a catabolic process by which a great variety of microorganisms can obtain energy as ATP. This is the process carried out by Saccharomyces cerevisiae, which is the most widely used microorganism in the industry nowadays, for the manufacture of a number of products such as bread, beer and wine. In addition, fermentation is classified according to the final product of the metabolic pathway, so different types are known, such as alcoholic, butyric and acetic fermentation, among others. Between the last mentioned, alcoholic fermentation is the most studied because of its relevance in the industry, so during this experimental practice it was aimed to achieve the production of different alcoholic beverages from three different fermentable carbon sources, in order to evaluate the alcohol content and other physicochemical parameters, and thus determine the effect of the carbon source or initial substrate in the fermentation process. For this, the preparation of the different musts, the activation of the yeast, its inoculation and later determination of the production of carbon dioxide and quantification of ethanol were carried out.

que facilitan el reconocimiento de posibles patrones presentes en ellos, como se muestra a continuación:
6/21/19, 3:24 PM - Meñeñotes 😽: Graficas
6/21/19, 3:25 PM - Meñeñotes 😽: Siguiendo con lo anterior, las gráficas presentadas permiten afirmar que, en general, la mayoría de encuestados fueron empleados de alguna compañía o empresa, de los cuales mas de la mitad no tenían un historial familiar de antecedentes de salud mental y una gran proporción trabajaba en una compañía tecnológica. Las gráficas obtenidas para las caracter´ısticas: treatment, no employees, care options, benefits,
mental health consequence, supervisor y mental vs physical tienen la informaci´on
distribu´ıda equitativamente entre sus categor´ıas. Por otro lado, phys health consequence
y mental health interview, self employed y obs consequence comparten las mismas
proporciones, y categor´ıas, como se observa en la Figura 5 y Figura 6. Respecto a estas ´ultimas
